(186, 2, '2016-01-20 02:06:31', '2016-01-20 02:06:31', '<b>Residents of Charleston Will Enjoy Faster, More Seamless Access to Medical Care with ZocDoc</b>\r\n\r\n<b>Charleston, SC – December 16, 2014 </b>– ZocDoc, the tech company at the beginning of a better healthcare experience, arrives in the Charleston area today, delivering faster access to quality medical care. With <a href="http://www.zocdoc.com/">ZocDoc</a>, patients can find in-network neighborhood doctors, instantly book appointments and fill out their paperwork online, see what other real patients have to say, get reminders for upcoming appointments and preventive checkups, and more.\r\n\r\nNot only does ZocDoc’s free service make the appointment-booking process much easier, it also makes it much faster despite a nationwide doctor shortage. This shortage – which has contributed to a national average wait time to see a physician of nearly three weeks – is particularly acute in South Carolina. The state ranks near the bottom nationally for the number of primary care doctors per resident, according to <a href="https://members.aamc.org/eweb/upload/State%20Physician%20Workforce%20Data%20Book%202013%20(PDF).pdf">a report</a> by the Association of American Medical Colleges.\r\n\r\nAnd according to <a href="http://www.coalitionforaccesstohealthcare.com/default.html">the Coalition for Access to Health Care</a>, more than 800,000 new patients are entering the South Carolina healthcare system under the Affordable Care Act this year, worsening the existing doctor shortage and strain on the healthcare system.\r\n\r\nZocDoc’s arrival will help South Carolina patients receive faster care by revealing the hidden supply of appointments in doctors’ calendars caused by cancellations and shifting schedules – up to 25 percent of a doctor’s day – and making them instantly available online. This transparency increases efficiency for local medical practices and reduces patients’ long wait times. The typical ZocDoc patient sees a doctor within 24 hours – far less than the national average of more than 18 days.\r\n\r\n“South Carolina patients are not alone in their difficulty to find the right doctor and quickly secure care,” said ZocDoc founder and CEO Cyrus Massoumi. “We are looking forward to making the healthcare process simpler and more efficient for them, as we do for millions of patients each month around the country.”\r\n\r\nTo access the ZocDoc marketplace, patients can visit the ZocDoc website (<a href="http://www.zocdoc.com/">www.zocdoc.com</a>) or the free ZocDoc mobile apps for <a href="https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/zocdoc-doctor-appointments/id391062219?mt=8">iPhone</a> or <a href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.zocdoc.android&amp;hl=en">Android</a> and enter their location, insurance, and the type of doctor they would like to see. They can also search by additional criteria, such as gender and languages spoken. ZocDoc shows neighborhood physicians’ real-time availability, qualifications and photos, and verified patient reviews. Patients select an available appointment time and click to book instantly.\r\n\r\nSouth Carolina patients can use ZocDoc Check-In to speed the paperwork process. Their medical history forms can be filled out online prior to a first appointment, and then travel with the patient from doctor to doctor – saving time and providing physicians with more complete and accurate patient information. ZocDoc email and text Appointment Reminders and personalized Wellness Reminders also help patients better manage their health.\r\n\r\nAt launch, patients can use <a href="https://www.zocdoc.com/">ZocDoc</a> to book appointments with participating South Carolina primary care doctors; dentists; obstetrician-gynecologists; dermatologists; and ear, nose, and throat doctors. Additional physicians and specialties will be added over the coming months. To learn more about ZocDoc, please visit the ZocDoc <a href="http://www.zocdoc.com/press">press room</a>. Follow the latest ZocDoc news on the <a href="http://blog.zocdoc.com/">ZocDoc blog</a>, via <a href="https://twitter.com/zocdoc">Twitter</a>, or on <a href="http://www.facebook.com/ZocDoc">Facebook</a>.\r\n\r\n<b>About ZocDoc</b>\r\n\r\nZocDoc is the tech company at the beginning of a better healthcare experience. Each month, millions of patients use ZocDoc to find in-network neighborhood doctors, instantly book appointments online, see what other real patients have to say, get reminders for upcoming appointments and preventive check-ups, fill out their paperwork online, and more. With a mission to give power to the patient, ZocDoc’s online marketplace delivers the accessible, seamless, and simple experience patients expect and deserve. ZocDoc is free for patients and available across the United States via <a href="https://www.zocdoc.com/">ZocDoc.com</a> or the ZocDoc app for <a href="https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/zocdoc-doctor-appointments/id391062219?mt=8">iPhone</a> and <a href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.zocdoc.android&amp;hl=en">Android.</a>', 'Zocdoc comes to South Carolina, helping patients find doctors and instantly book appointments online', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'zocdoc-comes-to-south-carolina-helping-patients-find-doctors-and-instantly-book-appointments-online', '', '', '2016-01-20 03:09:43', '2016-01-20 03:09:43', '', 0, 'http://zocdocstatic.wpengine.com/?post_type=press_releases&#038;p=186', 0, 'press_releases', '', 0),
(187, 2, '2016-01-20 02:10:13', '2016-01-20 02:10:13', '<b>Wasatch Residents Will Enjoy Faster, More Seamless Access to Healthcare with ZocDoc</b>\r\n\r\n<b>SALT LAKE CITY – Sept 24, 2014 </b>– <a href="https://www.zocdoc.com/">ZocDoc</a>, a free online service used by more than six million patients each month, arrives in Utah today, helping residents effortlessly secure faster access to quality healthcare. Wasatch patients can use ZocDoc.com or the free ZocDoc app to find in-network neighborhood doctors, read verified reviews and instantly book appointments online.\r\n\r\nNot only does ZocDoc’s free service make the appointment-booking process much easier, it also makes it much faster despite a nationwide doctor shortage. This shortage – which has contributed to a national average wait time to see a physician of nearly three weeks – is particularly acute in Utah. The state ranks in the bottom two nationally for the number of primary care doctors per resident, according to <a href="https://members.aamc.org/eweb/upload/State%20Physician%20Workforce%20Data%20Book%202013%20(PDF).pdf">a report</a> by the Association of American Medical Colleges.\r\n\r\nThe typical ZocDoc patient, however, sees a doctor in under 24 hours. ZocDoc helps uncover the “hidden supply” of appointments in doctors’ calendars caused by cancellations, no-shows and shifting schedules – up to 25 percent of a doctor’s day.\r\n\r\n“With residents feeling the effects of the current doctor shortage so greatly, it’s now more important than ever to bring ZocDoc to Utah,” said ZocDoc founder and CEO Cyrus Massoumi. “We’re excited to improve local patients’ access to quality care and help physicians increase the efficiency of their practices.”\r\n\r\nTo use this free service, patients can visit the ZocDoc website (<a href="https://www.zocdoc.com/">www.zocdoc.com</a>) or the free ZocDoc mobile apps for <a href="https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/zocdoc-doctor-appointments/id391062219?mt=8">iPhone</a> or <a href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.zocdoc.android&amp;hl=en">Android</a> and enter their location, insurance and the type of doctor they would like to see. ZocDoc shows local physicians’ real-time availability, qualifications, photos and verified patient reviews. Patients select an available appointment time and click to book instantly.\r\n\r\nPatients can use ZocDoc Check-In to speed the paperwork process. Their online personal and family medical history forms can be filled out prior to a first appointment and then travel with the patient from doctor to doctor – saving time and providing physicians with more complete and accurate patient information. ZocDoc email and text Appointment Reminders and personalized Wellness Reminders also help patients better manage their health.\r\n\r\nAt launch, Wasatch residents can use ZocDoc to book appointments with eight types of specialists including participating primary care doctors; obstetrician-gynecologists; dermatologists; ear, nose, and throat doctors; dentists; eye doctors; psychiatrists; and orthopedic surgeons. Additional physicians and specialties will continually be added to the service.\r\n\r\nTo learn more about ZocDoc, please visit the ZocDoc <a href="http://www.zocdoc.com/press">press room</a>. Follow the latest ZocDoc news on the <a href="http://blog.zocdoc.com/">ZocDoc blog</a>, via <a href="https://twitter.com/zocdoc">Twitter</a>, or on <a href="http://www.facebook.com/ZocDoc">Facebook</a>.\r\n\r\n<b>About ZocDoc</b>\r\n\r\nMore than six million patients use ZocDoc each month to find a nearby doctor or dentist, read verified reviews and health content, and instantly book appointments online. By revealing the “hidden supply” of appointments, ZocDoc helps patients receive faster access to care and optimizes doctors’ schedules. With ZocDoc Check-In, patients can fill out their paperwork online prior to their appointment, and physicians receive more complete and accurate patient information. ZocDoc is currently available in over 2,000 cities, and across more than 40 U.S. states. This service is free for patients via <a href="https://www.zocdoc.com/">ZocDoc.com</a> or free ZocDoc apps for <a href="https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/zocdoc-doctor-appointments/id391062219?mt=8">iPhone</a> and <a href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.zocdoc.android&amp;hl=en">Android</a>.', 'Zocdoc comes to Utah, helping patients find doctors and instantly book appointments online', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'zocdoc-comes-to-utah-helping-patients-find-doctors-and-instantly-book-appointments-online', '', '', '2016-01-20 03:09:49', '2016-01-20 03:09:49', '', 0, 'http://zocdocstatic.wpengine.com/?post_type=press_releases&#038;p=187', 0, 'press_releases', '', 0),
