(279, 2, '2016-01-20 14:55:16', '2016-01-20 14:55:16', '<b>From Geographic Differences to Online Physician Reviews, ZocDoc’s Insights Provide Snapshot of Country’s Health Behaviors in 2013</b>\r\n\r\n<b> NEW YORK, NY – December 5, 2013</b> – <a href="http://www.zocdoc.com">ZocDoc</a>, a service that helps patients receive faster access to care and optimizes doctors’ schedules, today released its second annual U.S. Health Checkup. Millions of patients each month use ZocDoc.com or the free ZocDoc apps to find nearby, in-network doctors and dentists, see their real-time availability, and instantly book appointments online. These online bookings have generated the country''s largest database of patient behavior, and ZocDoc tapped this information to share its insights into this year’s top health trends.\r\n\r\nZocDoc’s 2013 U.S. Health Checkup explored topics such as locations with the shortest and longest in-office wait times, markets that were the most proactive about their health, trends in online physician reviews, how male and female patient behavior differs, and many more. All findings are based on the percentage of total appointments booked via ZocDoc in 2013, and highlights include:\r\n\r\n<b>Geographic Trends</b>\r\n• Austin was most proactive in overall health, as measured by preventive appointment bookings.\r\n• San Francisco and Miami were respectively home to the most proactive men and women, as measured by preventive appointment bookings.\r\n• Denver patients made the most OB-GYN appointments.\r\n• Portland patients made the most allergy appointments and were also the most skin-conscious, as measured by dermatology appointment bookings.\r\n• San Francisco patients were best at maintaining their dental health, as measured by dentist appointment bookings.\r\n• Boston ranked the highest for eye health, as measured by eye doctor appointment bookings.\r\n• Northern New Jersey patients made the most dietician and nutritionist appointments.\r\n• Detroit patients made the most cosmetic appointments, and also booked the most appointments via their mobile devices.\r\n\r\n<b>Online Physician Review Trends</b>\r\n• The national average rating of a ZocDoc physician was 4.45 out of 5 stars.\r\n• Women rated doctors slightly higher than men, were less extreme with their star ratings, and left more comments with their ratings.\r\n• Men reviewed doctors more frequently and were slightly more forgiving on wait time.\r\n• Portland and San Antonio were two of the most vocal markets; Portland residents left the most ratings and San Antonio residents left the most comments with their ratings.\r\n• Northern New Jersey was most pleased with their doctors, giving them the highest average rating in the country at 4.86 out of 5 stars.\r\n\r\n<b>Appointment Time Trends &amp; Tips</b>\r\n• Most appointments were booked online between 11:30 AM and 12:00 PM – a time when doctors’ offices are typically getting ready to close for lunch.\r\n• The most popular appointment times were weekdays at 10:00 AM and 2:00 PM.\r\n• Specifically, men preferred Friday at 10:00 AM, while women preferred Monday at 2:00 PM.\r\n• The most popular day to see a doctor was Tuesday and the least popular day was Friday.\r\n• Tuesday was also the day with the most last-minute openings, making it a great day to secure an urgent appointment.\r\n• Seattle had the shortest in-office wait time, while Fort Myers had the longest.\r\n• Men attended more night and weekend appointments, while Long Island residents attended twice as many after-hour appointments than patients in other markets.\r\n• January was the most popular month to book an appointment.\r\n\r\n“We’re honored that over the past year, patients all across the country have turned to ZocDoc for so many of their healthcare needs,” said ZocDoc founder &amp; CEO Cyrus Massoumi. “We’re excited to share these patient-generated insights, as we think it provides an interesting view of the country’s health behaviors in 2013. We look forward to sharing this annual report in years to come, and we expect the findings will become increasingly robust as we continue to expand ZocDoc’s functionality and geographic footprint.”\r\n\r\nTo see the full report and infographic based on this data, visit the <a href="http://blog.zocdoc.com/zocdocs-2013-us-health-checkup-results">ZocDoc blog.</a>\r\n\r\n<b><u>About ZocDoc</u></b>\r\nMore than four million patients use ZocDoc each month to find a nearby doctor or dentist and instantly book an appointment online. By revealing the ''hidden supply'' of appointments, ZocDoc helps patients receive faster access to care and optimizes doctors’ schedules. With ZocDoc Check-In, patients can fill out their paperwork online prior to their appointment, and physicians receive more complete and accurate patient information. ZocDoc has raised $95 million in investments to date, is currently available in more than 1,900 cities, and covers 40 percent of the US population. This service is free for patients via <a href="http://www.zocdoc.com">ZocDoc.com</a> or the free ZocDoc app for <a href="https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/zocdoc-doctor-appointments/id391062219?mt=8">iPhone</a> and <a href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.zocdoc.android&amp;hl=en">Android</a>. A Spanish-language version called ZocDoc en Español is also available (<a href="https://espanol.zocdoc.com">espanol.zocdoc.com</a>; <a href="https://itunes.apple.com/es/app/zocdoc-doctor-appointments/id391062219?mt=8">iPhone</a> and <a href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.zocdoc.android&amp;hl=es">Android</a>).', 'Zocdoc releases 2013 S.S. Health Checkup, revealing this year’s top patient trends', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'zocdoc-releases-2013-s-s-health-checkup-revealing-this-years-top-patient-trends', '', '', '2016-01-20 14:55:28', '2016-01-20 14:55:28', '', 0, 'http://zocdocstatic.wpengine.com/?post_type=press_releases&#038;p=279', 0, 'press_releases', '', 0),
(280, 2, '2016-01-20 14:57:31', '2016-01-20 14:57:31', '<b>Healthcare providers are embracing online reviews, slowly adopting social media</b>\r\n\r\n<b>NEW YORK, NY – October 10, 2013</b> – <a href="http://zocdoc.com">ZocDoc</a>, a service that helps patients receive faster access to care and optimizes doctors’ schedules, today published the results of its first annual Digital Doctor Survey. This survey will keep a pulse on how physicians engage with various technologies year over year. The 2013 survey explored the use of online reviews, practice management technology, and social media among a sample of ZocDoc’s network of healthcare providers which included primary care doctors, dentists, obstetricians and gynecologists, dermatologists, podiatrists, dietitians, cardiologists, and more.\r\n\r\n<b>Online Reviews</b>\r\n<a href="http://www.reviewtrackers.com/heres-consumers-online-reviews-doctors-hospitals-health-care-services">Research</a> suggests that online reviews may significantly affect patients’ decisions when choosing their healthcare providers, and ZocDoc’s survey results show that the physicians are keenly aware of this. Eighty-five percent of respondents proactively monitor online reviews about themselves, and 36 percent look at their competitors’ reviews. Additionally, ZocDoc asked physicians to rank the fairness of online reviews on a scale of 1-10 and found the following:\r\n\r\n• 23 percent said they’re very fair (rating of 8-10)\r\n• 62 percent said they’re fair (rating of 4-7)\r\n• 15 percent said they’re not fair (rating of 1-3)\r\n\r\n“Patients are eager to access the healthcare system in the same way they engage with their favorite consumer brands, research hotels, or even book restaurants and flights, and it’s important for any physician practicing in today’s day and age to embrace this shift,” said Dr. Keri Peterson, an internal medicine specialist and a ZocDoc client of three years. “As people continue to depend on these reviews to make informed healthcare choices, it will become increasingly important for patients and doctors alike to know which systems close the loop and verify all of these reviews to ensure that they are trustworthy.”\r\n\r\n<b>Practice Management Technology</b>\r\nNew healthcare guidelines make it increasingly important for physicians to leverage technology to keep their practices connected. ZocDoc found that almost 75 percent of physicians surveyed have implemented a practice management system in their office. This is significantly higher than the <a href="http://www.hhs.gov/news/press/2013pres/05/20130522a.html">findings of the US Department of Health and Human Services</a>, which recently reported that roughly half of US physicians have implemented a practice management system.\r\n\r\n“ZocDoc clients tend to quickly adapt to the changing healthcare landscape in this digital world, which likely accounts for the disparity,” said ZocDoc Founder &amp; COO Oliver Kharraz, MD. “These healthcare providers are more aware of how they can utilize ZocDoc and other digital resources to improve their practices. Not only can technology improve office efficiency and enhance online reputations, but most importantly, they can improve patients’ access and care.”\r\n\r\n<b></b><b>Social Media</b>\r\nSocial media platforms are another tool which some physicians are choosing to employ to enhance their digital footprint. Some <a href="http://www.pwc.com/us/en/press-releases/2012/pwc-study-on-social-media-in-healthcare-press-release.jhtml">reports suggest</a> that nearly one-third of patients use social media sites for health-related matters, and that number is growing. This represents a sizable opportunity for physicians to not only promote their practices and connect with patients, but also stay in touch with each other and share educational information.\r\n\r\nZocDoc found that 53 percent of physicians surveyed have a Facebook account for their practice, 34 percent are using Google+, 28 percent are using LinkedIn, and 21 percent are using Twitter. Not surprisingly, overall social media usage is 22 percent higher among physicians between the ages of 26 and 55 than among physicians between 56 and 75 years of age. Thirty percent of practitioners report that they still do not have any social media presence.\r\n\r\n<b><u>About the Survey</u></b>\r\nA sample of ZocDoc healthcare providers received an email in July 2013 inviting them to take the survey. The survey was hosted by a third party vendor and received 360 responses. This annual survey will benchmark trends year over year.\r\n\r\n<b><u>About ZocDoc</u></b>\r\nMore than four million patients use ZocDoc each month to find a nearby doctor or dentist and instantly book an appointment online. By revealing the ''hidden supply'' of appointments, ZocDoc helps patients receive faster access to care and optimizes doctors’ schedules. With ZocDoc Check-In, patients can fill out their paperwork online prior to their appointment, and physicians receive more complete and accurate patient information. ZocDoc has raised $95 million in investments to date, is currently available in more than 1,900 cities, and covers 40 percent of the US population. This service is free for patients via <a href="http://www.zocdoc.com">ZocDoc.com</a> or the free ZocDoc apps for <a href="https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/zocdoc-doctor-appointments/id391062219?mt=8">iPhone</a> and <a href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.zocdoc.android&amp;hl=en">Android</a>. A Spanish-language version called ZocDoc en Español is also available (<a href="https://espanol.zocdoc.com">espanol.zocdoc.com</a>; <a href="https://itunes.apple.com/es/app/zocdoc-doctor-appointments/id391062219?mt=8">iPhone</a> and <a href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.zocdoc.android&amp;hl=es">Android</a>).', 'Zocdoc releases results of its first annual Digital Doctor Survey, benchmarking technology trends in healthcare', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'zocdoc-releases-results-of-its-first-annual-digital-doctor-survey-benchmarking-technology-trends-in-healthcare', '', '', '2016-01-20 15:04:09', '2016-01-20 15:04:09', '', 0, 'http://zocdocstatic.wpengine.com/?post_type=press_releases&#038;p=280', 0, 'press_releases', '', 0),
(281, 2, '2016-01-20 15:13:15', '2016-01-20 15:13:15', 'Oliver Kharraz, MD, is CEO and founder of ZocDoc. Oliver is the most recent doctor in a 300-year family tradition. Over the course of his wide-ranging career, Oliver has accrued comprehensive experience effecting change and building efficiency in large scale healthcare organizations using information technology.\r\n\r\nPrior to ZocDoc, Oliver was an Associate Principal at the global management consulting firm McKinsey &amp; Company. During his seven-year tenure at McKinsey &amp; Co., Oliver developed and implemented new patient utilization models for the national health services of a number of governments and major hospital chains.\r\n\r\nIn 1994, Oliver built and sold his first business – a forerunner of early internet software. He later became a resident doctor at the clinic of Ludwig Maximilian University in Munich, where he earned an MD and a Doctorate in Neuroscience. Oliver also has a Masters Degree in Philosophy from the Jesuit College of Philosophy in Munich.\r\n\r\nBorn in Germany, Oliver immigrated to the U.S. during his work for McKinsey &amp; Co. He currently resides in Brooklyn, NY, with his wife and their twin daughters.', 'Oliver Kharraz, MD', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'oliver-kharraz-md', '', '', '2016-01-29 23:43:29', '2016-01-29 23:43:29', '', 0, 'http://zocdocstatic.wpengine.com/?post_type=bios&#038;p=281', 0, 'bios', '', 0),
(282, 2, '2016-01-20 15:13:53', '2016-01-20 15:13:53', 'Nick Ganju is a founder at ZocDoc and leads strategic initiatives that address some of the company’s most impactful opportunities. He helped build ZocDoc because he believes that the power of technology can bring about a more efficient healthcare system. He has extensive experience in product development, database management and site architecture, including having personally built the earliest iterations of ZocDoc and directly overseeing its development for many of its first years.\r\n\r\nPrior to ZocDoc, Nick worked as the CTO of cfX, where he oversaw the design and implementation of financial software used by several Fortune 100 Wall Street firms. A Trilogy Development Alumnus, Nick previously lived in Silicon Valley. There, he played a pivotal role in the architecture and development of eBoodle (later acquired by BizRate), and in 2002 founded his first company, called Mixonic. He remained at Mixonic as the architect, manager, and lead programmer until moving to New York.\r\n\r\nNick was awarded an MBA from Columbia Business School in 2008. He also has a bachelor’s degree in Computer Science from the University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign. He first met ZocDoc founder Cyrus Massoumi when the two shared a desk at Trilogy Software.\r\n\r\nNick was born and raised in Chicago, and currently resides in New York. When he’s not working, the former Bay Area Amateur Billiards Champion can be found fronting his semi-professional cover band.', 'Nick Ganju', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'nick-ganju', '', '', '2016-01-29 23:43:15', '2016-01-29 23:43:15', '', 0, 'http://zocdocstatic.wpengine.com/?post_type=bios&#038;p=282', 0, 'bios', '', 0),
(283, 2, '2016-01-20 15:14:27', '2016-01-20 15:14:27', 'Cyrus Massoumi is the Chairman of the ZocDoc Board of Directors and founder of ZocDoc. After rupturing his eardrum in 2007 and spending four days searching for a doctor, he and co-founder Oliver Kharraz created ZocDoc to solve patient problems and improve the modern healthcare experience.\r\n\r\nPrior to ZocDoc, Cyrus served as an Engagement Manager at the global management consulting firm McKinsey &amp; Company, where he gained extensive experience in healthcare technology. It was at McKinsey &amp; Co. where Cyrus first met and collaborated with Oliver. Cyrus’s four-year tenure at McKinsey &amp; Co. began soon after his 2003 graduation from Columbia Business School, where he earned an MBA and received the Heffernan Award for Outstanding Service.\r\n\r\nIn 1999, Cyrus founded his first business, a web startup specializing in e-commerce management tools. During the prior year, he worked in Austin, Texas, for Trilogy Software, which recruited Cyrus upon his graduation, cum laude, from the Wharton School. It was at Trilogy where Cyrus met – and shared a desk with – ZocDoc founder Nick Ganju.\r\n\r\nA native of Florida, Cyrus also worked at Disney World, where he gained firsthand insight into the importance of excellent customer service – a learning he later implemented at ZocDoc which is central to the company’s operation today.\r\n\r\nCyrus currently resides in Manhattan. His most proud and humbling distinction to date is ZocDoc’s recognition as a Best Place to Work both in New York and Arizona.', 'Cyrus Massoumi', '', 'trash', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'cyrus-massoumi', '', '', '2016-01-22 15:12:28', '2016-01-22 15:12:28', '', 0, 'http://zocdocstatic.wpengine.com/?post_type=bios&#038;p=283', 0, 'bios', '', 0),
(284, 2, '2016-01-20 15:15:16', '2016-01-20 15:15:16', 'Netta Samroengraja is Chief Financial Officer and Chief People Officer of ZocDoc. As CFO, Netta brings nearly 15 years of experience in finance and operations to ZocDoc and oversees finance and accounting. As CPO, Netta also oversees talent and maintaining ZocDoc''s culture and core values. Netta joined ZocDoc in 2008 because she believes that our healthcare system can be improved by dedicated people.\r\n\r\nPrior to ZocDoc, Netta was the Chief Operating Officer of Next Jump, an ecommerce marketing services company. She worked for Next Jump for over five years, having previously held the position of Vice President of Finance. Netta was previously an Associate at Boston Ventures and an Analyst at Bear Stearns, where she developed expertise in venture capital and investment banking.\r\n\r\nNetta received an MBA in Finance from University of Pennsylvania’s Wharton School of Business in 2003. She was also awarded a bachelor’s degree in Economics and Operations Research from Columbia University in 1996.\r\n\r\nOriginally from Westchester County, New York, Netta now resides in New York City.', 'Netta Samroengraja', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'netta-samroengraja', '', '', '2016-01-29 23:43:00', '2016-01-29 23:43:00', '', 0, 'http://zocdocstatic.wpengine.com/?post_type=bios&#038;p=284', 0, 'bios', '', 0),
(285, 2, '2016-01-20 15:15:46', '2016-01-20 15:15:46', 'Ori Schnaps is the Vice President of Engineering at ZocDoc, where he fosters collaboration among his team of designers and engineers to build quality products for the digital health marketplace.\r\n\r\nOri has more than a decade of experience developing elegant solutions to complex business problems. Before ZocDoc, he served as the Global Head of Technology at Thompson Reuters, where he oversaw a 350 person team to build a next generation product for a $1B investment and advisory market.\r\n\r\nPrior, Ori co-founded Thrive, a company dedicated to helping people in their 20s and 30s gain control of their financial life. As Chief Technology Officer, he managed the technical, product, and design processes. Within 24 months of raising capital and building the product, Ori and his team sold their company to Tree.com, where Ori then managed the development of new products using the Thrive platform.\r\n\r\nOri has worked at companies including Goldman Sachs; Pronto, Inc., a comparison shopping engine; TSYS Prepaid.com card solution built on the VISA backbone; and Bluewave USA, an interactive agency based in New York City.\r\n\r\nOri earned a BS in Computer Science with a minor in Mathematics from Hofstra University. Born in Israel, he currently resides in New York City with his wife Anne, their twin daughters, and their cats Cheddar and Queso Bandito.', 'Ori Schnaps', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'ori-schnaps', '', '', '2016-01-29 23:42:31', '2016-01-29 23:42:31', '', 0, 'http://zocdocstatic.wpengine.com/?post_type=bios&#038;p=285', 0, 'bios', '', 0),
(286, 2, '2016-01-20 15:16:20', '2016-01-20 15:16:20', 'Joaquin Gamboa is the Vice President of Legal Affairs at ZocDoc, bringing with him 15 years of domestic and international experience advising technology-focused businesses ranging from startups to Fortune 100 companies.\r\n\r\nAt ZocDoc, Joaquin oversees all legal matters and provides counsel that fosters compliant innovation and ensures robust and secure systems.\r\n\r\nPrior to joining ZocDoc, Joaquin was a Partner at the prestigious Levine, Blaszak, Block &amp; Boothby (LB3) law firm where he represented multiple Fortune 100 companies on cloud computing, software licensing and other technology-related deals, and where he served as a strategic advisor to early stage technology companies, providing forward-thinking counsel on business model formation, business development, and capital raising initiatives.\r\n\r\nBefore making his way to LB3, Joaquin served as Director of Business Development at Yodlee, a premier financial technology provider. There, he led the strategic alliances team and headed international business development. Joaquin also has experience as an operator, having been a founding partner at Bay Area Ventures, a fund focused on facilitating Latin American investment in Silicon Valley. Joaquin started his career at Brobeck, Phleger &amp; Harrison, a top-tier national law firm based in the San Francisco Bay Area and noted for its technology expertise.\r\n\r\nJoaquin received a B.A. in Philosophy from The University of California at Berkeley in 1994, and a J.D. from Stanford Law School in 1998.\r\n\r\nHaving grown up between Mexico City and San Diego, Joaquin now resides in New York City. While not at work, he dedicates his time to his wife and three children.', 'Joaquin Gamboa', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'joaquin-gamboa', '', '', '2016-01-29 23:42:04', '2016-01-29 23:42:04', '', 0, 'http://zocdocstatic.wpengine.com/?post_type=bios&#038;p=286', 0, 'bios', '', 0),
(287, 2, '2016-01-20 15:19:08', '2016-01-20 15:19:08', 'Anna Elwood is the Vice President of Operations at ZocDoc, where she oversees our service delivery teams across three office locations. With a passion for people, Anna spends her time at ZocDoc maintaining an award-winning customer service team that she built from the ground up.\r\n\r\nHer teams focus on creating a seamless healthcare experience for ZocDoc’s patients and doctors, maintaining ZocDoc’s high customer satisfaction scores and resetting expectations for healthcare service. She values strong hiring and training, fast and thorough execution, close collaboration across departments, and creative problem solving.\r\n\r\nAnna was one of ZocDoc’s earliest employees, joining the company after working for Apple, where she focused on customer service and training in technology. Anna also has a background in the arts, education and non-profit sectors. She received a Master’s in Fine Arts from Pennsylvania State University and a Bachelor’s in Fine Arts, with a double major in Literature, from Adelphi University.\r\n\r\nOriginally from the Berkshires in Massachusetts, Anna enjoys the outdoors, brewing beer, and spending time with her wife and son.', 'Anna Elwood', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'anna-elwood', '', '', '2016-02-04 16:13:10', '2016-02-04 16:13:10', '', 0, 'http://zocdocstatic.wpengine.com/?post_type=bios&#038;p=287', 0, 'bios', '', 0),
(288, 2, '2016-01-20 15:19:45', '2016-01-20 15:19:45', 'Richard Fine is Vice President of Marketing at ZocDoc. In his role, he manages the company’s brand and marketing efforts. Richard leads the team in building ZocDoc’s passionate community of patients and providers.\r\n\r\nBoth professors of medicine, Richard’s parents are delighted to see him return to healthcare. Much to their distress, he spent most of his career working on branding and marketing in nearly every other sector.\r\n\r\nRichard got his start in advertising at Saatchi &amp; Saatchi and was an early employee and partner at the brand innovation agency Redscout. There, Richard’s work centered on the belief that the best way to change a consumer’s perception of a brand is to change the way they experience it. He led product- and brand-focused work for the likes of PepsiCo, Nike, Diageo and Johnson &amp; Johnson, among others. Redscout grew to be an industry leader and was acquired by MDC Partners.\r\n\r\nRichard also founded Help Remedies, a consumer healthcare company that makes over-the-counter medicine simpler and friendlier. Under Richard’s leadership, Help rapidly expanded nationally to retailers including Duane Reade, Walgreens, Target and W Hotels, leading to its acquisition. The company won an IDEA award for packaging, a Cannes Lion for advertising and a best of show from Dieline and was selected as one of Wallpaper Magazine’s Life Enhancers of the Year.\r\n\r\nRichard graduated with First Class Honors from Oxford University with a BA in Philosophy, Politics and Economics. He lives in New York City with his wife and two children.', 'Richard Fine', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'richard-fine', '', '', '2016-01-29 23:41:27', '2016-01-29 23:41:27', '', 0, 'http://zocdocstatic.wpengine.com/?post_type=bios&#038;p=288', 0, 'bios', '', 0),
(289, 2, '2016-01-20 15:20:18', '2016-01-20 15:20:18', 'Kevin Kumler is Vice President of Health Systems at ZocDoc, leading the company’s hospitals and health systems business, which has doubled under his leadership.\r\n\r\nFrom a medical family of orthopedists, pediatricians and dental hygiene faculty, Kevin took to the business side of healthcare. He brings 15 years of experience to hospital and health system clients—applying his entrepreneurial spirit and deep healthcare industry knowledge to help clients improve their patients’ experience while growing their revenues.\r\n\r\nPrior to leading ZocDoc’s hospital and health systems team, Kevin led ZocDoc’s local sales team helping the company expand its footprint nationwide.\r\n\r\nPrior to joining ZocDoc, Kevin was an Associate Principal in McKinsey &amp; Company’s healthcare practice. During his ten years at McKinsey, Kevin served large health systems, insurance companies and government organizations in the United States, United Kingdom and India. Kevin also worked in business development and strategy at Mount Carmel Health, part of the Trinity Health System in Columbus, Ohio.\r\n\r\nKevin received his MBA from Stanford University and BA in Mathematics-Economics from Wesleyan University in Connecticut. He lives in New Jersey with his wife and their three highly energetic children.', 'Kevin Kumler', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'kevin-kumler', '', '', '2016-01-29 23:41:07', '2016-01-29 23:41:07', '', 0, 'http://zocdocstatic.wpengine.com/?post_type=bios&#038;p=289', 0, 'bios', '', 0),
(290, 2, '2016-01-20 15:20:45', '2016-01-20 15:20:45', 'Andre Heeg is Vice President of Local Sales at ZocDoc, leading the team managing the company’s 50-state footprint of local doctors and private medical practices.\r\n\r\nLeveraging his deep experience as a medical doctor and a business consultant, Andre is focused on driving new business, cultivating the development of his team members, and creating a culture of success within the sales structure.\r\n\r\nAndre joined ZocDoc in 2013 after serving as a consultant for McKinsey &amp; Company, working exclusively on projects in the healthcare space, including med tech and pharmaceuticals. Prior to McKinsey, Andre studied medicine and dentistry, with a focus on transplant immunobiology and bioengineering. He earned his MD and PhD in Medicine from Julius-Maximilians-University Wuerzburg and Heidelberg and then his DDS and PhD in Dentistry from Albert-Ludwigs-University Freiburg im Breisgau. After his studies, Andre worked as a resident in maxilla-facial surgery at the Katharinenhospital Stuttgart.\r\n\r\nBorn and raised in Germany, Andre has always had a passion for other cultures and languages and has studied and worked abroad extensively. He is a former German champion in freestyle wrestling and loves sports, including mountaineering, CrossFit, snowboarding and skiing.', 'Andre Heeg, MD, DDS', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'andre-heeg-md-dds', '', '', '2016-01-29 23:40:50', '2016-01-29 23:40:50', '', 0, 'http://zocdocstatic.wpengine.com/?post_type=bios&#038;p=290', 0, 'bios', '', 0),
(291, 2, '2016-01-20 15:21:17', '2016-01-20 15:21:17', 'Todd Edebohls is the Vice President of Business Development at ZocDoc. Todd brings deep expertise in developing high-growth internet companies, leveraging his two decades as a business development and general management executive.\r\n\r\nWith Amazon from 1999 to 2007, Todd led $300 million of business development throughout the U.S., Europe, Japan, and China. He led teams that built the company’s flowers, photos, and travel businesses and drove negotiations that helped build its health, apparel, sports, jewelry, and beauty businesses. He also created and led teams of 60 people across 15 departments that made and managed enterprise services agreements in the U.S. and Europe.\r\n\r\nFrom his office at the D. E. Shaw investment firm in 2008 and 2009, Todd was Chairman of the Board of Directors of its Nasdaq-traded company of Toys.com and eToys. After he helped the board and management explore its strategic direction and exit options, he led the sale of the company in transactions that included the fourth-highest domain name sale in history.\r\n\r\nTodd was also founder and CEO of Inside Jobs, an education software startup that Forbes twice named a ‘Top Website For Your Career’ and Chegg (NYSE: CHGG) acquired in 2013. He started his internet business career with PointCast in 1997, earned his Bachelor of Science at Cornell University, and was, long ago, a New York State Emergency Medical Technician.', 'Todd Edebohls', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'todd-edebohls', '', '', '2016-01-29 23:40:25', '2016-01-29 23:40:25', '', 0, 'http://zocdocstatic.wpengine.com/?post_type=bios&#038;p=291', 0, 'bios', '', 0),
(292, 2, '2016-01-20 15:21:48', '2016-01-20 15:21:48', 'Melissa Esmundo is Vice President of Acquisition and CRM at ZocDoc. With more than 15 years of marketing and brand strategy experience, she manages the company’s digital and offline media, CRM, marketing analytics and research. Her team is focused on understanding the needs of customers and driving acquisition and retention across all of ZocDoc’s products. At ZocDoc, Melissa passionately believes in the power of people and technology to reinvent the healthcare experience.\r\n\r\nPrior to joining ZocDoc, Melissa founded her own consultancy, MM Strategic Advisors, where she advised a range of companies from early stage venture-backed start-ups to global multi-billion dollar organizations on brand positioning, customer journey, acquisition and retention. Previously, she led marketing at Tough Mudder, encouraging thousands of participants across the globe to get fit and stay healthy.\r\n\r\nMelissa began her career in retail apparel at Gap Inc., developing and driving customer-centric retail, business and marketing strategies and later moved on to consulting with Prophet Brand Strategy. At Prophet, Melissa led client engagements across various sectors including healthcare, hospitality, packaged goods, agriculture, finance and pharmaceuticals.\r\n\r\nMelissa graduated from the John M. Olin School of Business at Washington University in St. Louis with a BS/BA in Marketing, International Business and French and from the Leonard N. Stern School of Business at New York University with an MBA. She lives in Brooklyn with her wife and incredibly tiny Chihuahua, Gracie.', 'Melissa Esmundo', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'melissa-esmundo', '', '', '2016-01-29 23:39:56', '2016-01-29 23:39:56', '', 0, 'http://zocdocstatic.wpengine.com/?post_type=bios&#038;p=292', 0, 'bios', '', 0),
(293, 2, '2016-01-20 15:22:14', '2016-01-20 15:22:14', 'Colleen Gangl is Vice President of People at ZocDoc. She leads the company’s recruiting, people operations, and talent development efforts.\r\n\r\nColleen brings to ZocDoc more than 14 years of human resources experience, including as a strategic partner to several major media and retail companies. Most recently, she was a consultant to small and medium-sized companies, providing their HR teams with strategic counsel and guidance. With a strong track record of building trusting relationships, Colleen is passionate about finding solutions to help organizations work smarter, implementing efficient processes, and building better organizational structures to create happy and productive teams.\r\n\r\nColleen began her career as a receptionist for her father’s medical practice and afterwards, became an HR generalist for major retail brands including H&amp;M and Ann Taylor. Colleen then decided to shift towards the digital media industry, joining Getty Images’ HR team. During her more than six years there, Colleen oversaw HR programs, employee development initiatives, acquisition integrations, crisis management and issues resolution for the organization.\r\n\r\nColleen graduated from the University of Delaware with a BA in Art History and from Rutgers University School of Management and Labor Relations with a Masters in Human Resources Management. She enjoys yoga, hiking with her dog and spending time with her family. She lives in New Jersey with her husband and their daughters.', 'Colleen Gangl', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'colleen-gangl', '', '', '2016-01-29 23:39:27', '2016-01-29 23:39:27', '', 0, 'http://zocdocstatic.wpengine.com/?post_type=bios&#038;p=293', 0, 'bios', '', 0),
(294, 2, '2016-01-20 15:22:47', '2016-01-20 15:22:47', 'Kate is the Vice President of Finance at ZocDoc. With more than 15 years of experience in financial planning and strategy, she oversees the company’s finance team.\r\n\r\nPrior to coming to ZocDoc, Kate worked at top media and internet companies including IAC, Condé Nast and HBO. In her most recent role, she led the financial planning and analysis team at IAC, working with executives and financial leadership across the company’s portfolio of brands which includes Match.com, Vimeo and HomeAdvisor. Kate began her career at PricewaterhouseCoopers.\r\n\r\nShe earned a Masters in Accounting and a BS in Business Administration from the University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill. Originally from Maryland, Kate resides in Manhattan. She loves live music and is an avid Tar Heel basketball fan.', 'Kate Sigman', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'kate-sigman', '', '', '2016-01-29 23:39:00', '2016-01-29 23:39:00', '', 0, 'http://zocdocstatic.wpengine.com/?post_type=bios&#038;p=294', 0, 'bios', '', 0),
(295, 2, '2016-01-20 15:23:14', '2016-01-20 15:23:14', 'Myles is Chief of Staff at ZocDoc. In this role he works with the executive team to set strategy and drive execution.\r\n\r\nMyles joins ZocDoc from Millennial Media, a mobile advertising marketplace, where he was SVP of Business Operations. He spent nearly a decade at McKinsey &amp; Company, leading efforts to increase operational and salesforce effectiveness across the media, high tech, and financial services industries. Myles began his career in the non-profit sector, where over ten years he launched and led programs addressing homelessness and affordable housing.\r\n\r\nMyles earned MBA and JD degrees from Northwestern University and a BA in Interdisciplinary Studies from the University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill. Originally from Kentucky, he lives in Brooklyn with his husband and two daughters.', 'Myles Presler', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'myles-presler', '', '', '2016-01-29 23:38:32', '2016-01-29 23:38:32', '', 0, 'http://zocdocstatic.wpengine.com/?post_type=bios&#038;p=295', 0, 'bios', '', 0),
(296, 2, '2016-01-20 15:23:45', '2016-01-20 15:23:45', 'Serkan is Vice President of Engineering, Software Architecture at ZocDoc. With more than 17 years of professional software development experience, he is responsible for ZocDoc’s technical roadmap and strategy, and scaling software architecture and systems.\r\n\r\nSerkan comes from a family steeped in healthcare. His front-row view of the pain points in both the patient and provider experiences spurred a personal passion to improve the current system through technology and his work at ZocDoc.\r\n\r\nBefore joining ZocDoc, Serkan was a technical leader for a team of more than 70 developers across four locations at Amazon working to define and design the ecommerce leader’s architectural strategy for Catalog and Selection Systems.\r\n\r\nPrior to his time at Amazon, Serkan spent three years at Goldman Sachs building trading systems that are powered by real-time social media analytics insights and unified communications – a first in Wall Street.\r\n\r\nSerkan began his career at Microsoft, where he spent more than 10 years. He served as an engineering manager on the Windows team and later a manager of the core development team which shipped the first five major releases of Microsoft OCS/Lync Service, a product that reached $1 billion in revenue faster than any other Microsoft product before it.\r\n\r\nSerkan graduated with a BS in Computer Science from Bilkent University in Turkey, where he is originally from. He has lived in New York City for eight years and currently resides in Brooklyn with his wife and daughter.', 'Serkan Kutan', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'serkan-kutan', '', '', '2016-01-29 23:38:07', '2016-01-29 23:38:07', '', 0, 'http://zocdocstatic.wpengine.com/?post_type=bios&#038;p=296', 0, 'bios', '', 0),
(373, 2, '2016-01-21 03:25:37', '2016-01-21 03:25:37', '<b>ZocDoc’s New Online Resource Empowers Patients to Make More Informed Healthcare Decisions</b>\r\n\r\n<b>NEW YORK, NY – August 15, 2013</b> – <a href="http://zocdoc.com">ZocDoc</a>, a free service for patients to find doctors and book appointments instantly online, today introduced the <a href="http://healthmarketplace.zocdoc.com">ZocDoc Health Marketplace Resource</a>. This destination provides easy-to-digest information regarding the upcoming Health Insurance Marketplaces created under the Affordable Care Act. The goal of this resource is to provide people with independent information and analysis to help them make informed healthcare choices. ZocDoc created this resource to help raise awareness of the new health insurance marketplaces, and better equip individuals to:\r\n\r\n• Learn more about health insurance marketplaces;\r\n• Better understand which plans offer the best access to medical providers with availability;\r\n• Determine which level of coverage might be best for them and their families;\r\n\r\nZocDoc has always worked to improve patients’ access to care and bring efficiency and transparency to the healthcare system, and this new initiative is no exception. Over the course of the company’s nearly six year history, millions of patients have come to view ZocDoc as their personal health ally. As 30 million new patients prepare to enter the system, ZocDoc aims to help them more easily navigate the healthcare space – just as they do for the millions of people who currently use the company’s free service each month.\r\n\r\n“We’re excited to be able to offer this resource to those exploring enrollment in these new health plans,” said ZocDoc founder and COO Oliver Kharraz, MD. “With lots of new information and up to 100 different choices in some marketplaces, navigating this new space may seem daunting. Our aim is to make it easier for the 30 million new patients entering the system to easily access the care they need and deserve.”\r\n\r\nThe key features of the ZocDoc Health Marketplace Resource include:\r\n\r\n• <b>Care Access Grades</b> – Letter grades assigned to each health insurer that indicate how easy it will be for patients to secure near-term appointments with in-network medical providers. Since many plans on the marketplaces will have narrow networks, it is especially important for patients to be able to evaluate the availability of care under each insurer.\r\n• <b>State-specific Information</b> – An overview of what plans are available under each state’s health insurance marketplace.\r\n• <b>FAQs </b>– Answers to common questions, covering a broad array of topics ranging from what a health insurance marketplace is and how it works to how much patients should expect to pay for insurance premiums and more.\r\n• <b>Glossary</b> – Easy-to-understand definitions of common insurance and healthcare industry-related terms, helping patients cut through the jargon and obtain a better practical understanding of the system and its components.\r\n• <b>Health Insurance Giveaway</b> – ZocDoc is giving away health insurance coverage for one individual for one year. To enter for a chance to win, visitors simply need to submit an email address.\r\n\r\nWith the nation’s largest real-time database of available appointments that patients can instantly book online, ZocDoc is in a unique position to provide the most accurate, up-to-date insight into doctor availability and help people evaluate the level of access to care under each health insurance plan in their state’s insurance marketplace. Amid the influx of new information about the insurance system, ZocDoc hopes to lend its expertise to eliminate potential confusion, encourage positive action, and empower more people to obtain the medical care they need. Patients can find the Resource at <a href="http://healthmarketplace.zocdoc.com">healthmarketplace.zocdoc.com</a>.\r\n\r\nZocDoc will allow patients to book with the vast majority of the newly created health insurance plans across the +1,800 cities and towns where the service is currently live. Patients covered under these new insurance plans can begin making appointments with in-network doctors starting in January 2014 on www.zocdoc.com.\r\n\r\n<b><u>About ZocDoc</u></b>\r\nMillions of patients each month use ZocDoc to find a nearby doctor or dentist and instantly book an appointment online. The company’s most recent product, ZocDoc Check-In, allows patients to fill out their paperwork online in advance of their appointment. By revealing the ''hidden supply'' of appointments, ZocDoc helps patients receive faster access to care and optimizes doctors’ schedules. ZocDoc has raised $95 million in investments to date and is currently available in more than 1,800 cities and covers 40 percent of the US population. This service is free for patients via <a href="http://www.zocdoc.com">ZocDoc.com</a> or the free ZocDoc apps for <a href="https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/zocdoc-doctor-appointments/id391062219?mt=8">iPhone</a> and <a href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.zocdoc.android&amp;hl=en">Android</a>. A Spanish-language version called ZocDoc en Español is also available (<a href="https://espanol.zocdoc.com/">espanol.zocdoc.com</a>; <a href="https://itunes.apple.com/es/app/zocdoc-doctor-appointments/id391062219?mt=8">iPhone</a> and <a href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.zocdoc.android&amp;hl=es">Android</a>).', 'Zocdoc Health Marketplace Resource helps patients navigate new health insurance exchanges', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'zocdoc-health-marketplace-resource-helps-patients-navigate-new-health-insurance-exchanges', '', '', '2016-01-21 03:26:10', '2016-01-21 03:26:10', '', 0, 'http://zocdocstatic.wpengine.com/?post_type=press_releases&#038;p=373', 0, 'press_releases', '', 0);
