(392, 2, '2016-01-21 14:55:50', '2016-01-21 14:55:50', '<b>Austin Patients Enjoy Improved Access to Medical Care with ZocDoc</b>\r\n\r\n<b>AUSTIN, TEXAS – March 19, 2012</b> – Today ZocDoc launches in Greater Austin with the mission of improving access to medical care in the area. ZocDoc, a free service for patients, is a one-stop resource for researching doctors and making appointments instantly online. At launch, the service offers appointments with participating primary care doctors, obstetrician-gynecologists and dermatologists throughout the Austin area.\r\n\r\nTo use the service, patients visit the ZocDoc website (<a href="http://www.zocdoc.com">www.zocdoc.com</a>) or use one of the free ZocDoc apps to enter their location, insurance plan, and the type of healthcare provider they would like to see. ZocDoc then shows each doctor’s schedule in real-time, along with credentials and patient reviews, to help patients choose the practitioner who best fits their needs. Patients simply select a timeslot and complete a brief checkout process to book an appointment. ZocDoc then sends email and text message reminders to help patients remember to attend their doctor visits. ZocDoc also offers free applications for <a href="http://itunes.apple.com/us/app/zocdoc-doctor-appointments/id391062219?mt=8">iPhone</a>, <a href="http://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.zocdoc.android&amp;hl=en">Android</a>, and <a href="http://appworld.blackberry.com/webstore/content/62021/?lang=en">BlackBerry</a>, allowing patients to find doctors and make appointments on the go.\r\n\r\nCyrus Massoumi, ZocDoc founder and CEO, worked in Austin for Trilogy Software after graduating from University of Pennsylvania. “It is particularly exciting to bring ZocDoc’s service to Austin, where I spent my early career and met ZocDoc co-founder and Chief Technology Officer, Nick Ganju,” said Massoumi. “Austin’s tech-savvy doctors and patients coupled with ZocDoc’s previous success in Dallas-Fort Worth a