(707, 2, '2016-01-29 21:09:31', '2016-01-29 21:09:31', 'Dr. Keri Peterson is a practicing physician and ZocDoc media spokesperson. She partners with ZocDoc to offer her expert medical advice and insights for patients and doctors. Since 1999, Dr. Peterson has been in private practice with a prominent medical group in Manhattan. Specializing in Internal Medicine, she holds appointments at Lenox Hill Hospital and Mount Sinai Medical Center and is a member of the American College of Physicians and American Medical Association.\r\n\r\nDr. Peterson obtained her bachelor degree from Cornell University and received her medical degree from Mount Sinai School of Medicine. She completed her post-graduate training in Internal Medicine at Mount Sinai Medical Center in New York City and is board certified in Internal Medicine. Additionally, Dr. Peterson has received specialized training and certification for select cosmetic procedures.\r\n\r\nWith a commitment to the advancement of medicine, Dr. Peterson has contributed to several leading medical and scientific journals and has presented at distinguished medical symposiums. Alongside her work with ZocDoc, Dr. Peterson is a medical contributor and columnist for Women’s Health Magazine, a regular guest on The Today Show and has appeared on Dr. Oz, The Rachael Ray Show, Fox News, Good Morning America, The Meredith Show, The Katie Show, America’s Newsroom, Fox 5 News, America’s News HQ, Neil Cavuto, CNN and Nancy Grace.', 'Dr. Keri Peterson', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'dr-keri-peterson', '', '', '2016-01-29 23:37:28', '2016-01-29 23:37:28', '', 0, 'http://zocdocstatic.wpengine.com/?post_type=bios&#038;p=707', 0, 'bios', '', 0),
